# --- Local ASI:One perception agent (run fetch-agents/perception/agent.py) ---
# Get key: https://asi1.ai/developer
# perception/agent.py loads this file automatically (and repo-root .env); no need to duplicate in PowerShell unless you prefer.
# ASI1_API_KEY=
# Optional: cap Perception user prompt size if ASI returns 400 (default 95000 in agent.py); env ASI_USER_MESSAGE_MAX_CHARS
# BOOMER_AGENT_NAME=Boomer-Cognitive
# BOOMER_AGENT_SEED=your-unique-secret-seed-phrase
# BOOMER_AGENT_PORT=8001
# BOOMER_MAILBOX=true   # only after Agent inspector mailbox is connected
# BOOMER_AGENT_NETWORK=testnet   # optional: if mainnet Almanac registration lacks funds
#
# --- Boomer Node → Python query bridge → local or hosted agent address ---
# Install: py -3.12 -m pip install -r fetch-agents/requirements-query-bridge.txt
# voice.js loads this file via backend/src/loadEnv.js (not cwd), so dev:all from repo root still works.
# Cognitive uAgent address for query_bridge. Perception-only: Perception agent1q…
# Drift→(optional Memory)→Perception: point at hosted Drift agent1q…
# On Drift set PERCEPTION_AGENT_ADDRESS; optional MEMORY_AGENT_ADDRESS = Boomer Memory agent (see fetch-agents/memory/agent.py).
# On Memory set ASI1_API_KEY + PERCEPTION_AGENT_ADDRESS.
# AGENTVERSE_PERCEPTION_ADDRESS=agent1q…
# AGENTVERSE_QUERY_PYTHON=py -3.12
# query_bridge: default uses a short-lived signing Identity (agent…) for Agentverse; set to restore user… sender:
# BOOMER_QUERY_USER_SENDER=1
# Optional stable bridge identity (same seed → same agent1q… address):
# BOOMER_QUERY_AGENT_SEED=your-unique-bridge-seed-phrase
# Optional custom REST entry only: AGENTVERSE_COGNITIVE_REST_URL=https://…
# GET /cognitive/agentverse — holistic: browsing + memory narrative + browser heuristics + wellness + drift → ASI:One (tagged sections). Cache TTL ms (0 = disable):
# FETCH_HOLISTIC_CACHE_MS=90000
# Optional: Perception agent (fetch-agents/perception/agent.py) — headlines appended to snapshot text for ASI.
# Optional: Cognitive insight card (Node researchNewsBrief.js) prefers SerpApi when SERPAPI_API_KEY is set.
# Auto headline provider: SerpApi → NewsAPI.org → NewsData (first matching key). Force one:
# NEWS_HEADLINES_PROVIDER=serpapi   # | newsapi | newsdata (newsdata + sole NEWSDATA_API_KEY = newsdata.io key)
# https://serpapi.com/manage-api-key — Google Search JSON API (see https://serpapi.com/search-api )
# SERPAPI_API_KEY=
# SERPAPI_GOOGLE_NEWS=1
# SERPAPI_HL=en
# SERPAPI_GL=us
# https://newsapi.org/account
# NEWS_API_KEY=
# https://newsdata.io — explicit key (recommended for cognitive-insight card + avoiding mis-named vars)
# NEWSDATA_IO_API_KEY=
# Legacy name: often holds newsapi.org key (alias when NEWS_API_KEY empty); else second key with NEWS_API_KEY for NewsData.io
# NEWSDATA_API_KEY=
# Shared tuning:
# NEWS_API_POLL_SECONDS=86400
# NEWS_API_QUERY=dementia OR alzheimer OR cognitive health
# NEWS_API_PAGE_SIZE=5
# Re-fetch before ASI:One Chat if cache empty or older than this many seconds (hosted agents often have no shared RAM between workers; default 300).
# NEWS_HEADLINES_MAX_AGE_CHAT_SEC=300
# Extra NewsData call per chat when the user asks for news / health topics (uses their wording as `q`). Default on; set 0 to disable.
# NEWS_CHAT_ONDEMAND=1
# NewsData free tier query length cap (characters). Default 100 per their developer plan.
# NEWSDATA_Q_MAX_CHARS=100
# Optional: search string for the cognitive-insight card on the app (defaults to NEWS_API_QUERY or a brain-health preset).
# NEWS_INSIGHT_QUERY=alzheimer OR dementia OR brain health
# Curated evidence themes (WHO/NIA links, grounding rules) are appended to memory_context from backend/data/perception-evidence-brief.txt.
# Optional: extra text for hosted Perception only — set Agent secret BOOMER_RESEARCH_BRIEF (see fetch-agents/README.md).

# Memory Anchor agent (Python) — same URL works for Fetch.ai / Agentverse deployment
FETCHAI_CONTINUITY_AGENT_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8099/v1/continuity

# Optional Bearer token for the agent HTTP endpoint
# FETCHAI_CONTINUITY_API_KEY=

# Routines / caregiver negotiation (POST JSON: context + physicalSnapshot). Optional — without URL, Node uses local copy.
# Run stub: python backend/fetchai_routines_agent/main.py  (default port 8098)
# FETCHAI_ROUTINES_AGENT_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8098/
# FETCHAI_ROUTINES_API_KEY=

# Set on the machine where fetchai_continuity_agent runs (Python), not required for Node-only local rules
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# Extension "Who?" button: OpenAI vision + page text vs Loved only (no DeepFace). Requires this key; restart voice server after setting.
# MEMORY_ANCHOR_USE_LLM=true

# Optional: command for face matching (extension scan). Default: python (Windows) / python3 (Unix)
# PYTHON_FACE_MATCH=python

# Bind the voice API on all interfaces (sometimes fixes Chrome/Edge extensions not reaching loopback):
# BOOMER_LISTEN_HOST=0.0.0.0
# (Default is 127.0.0.1 only.)

# Optional: SQLite activity database (if you use migrated visits). Default: backend/data/activity.db
# GET /routine/flow reads this when the file exists; otherwise uses activity.json visits.
# BOOMER_ACTIVITY_DB=C:\path\to\activity.db

# Loved ones (browser extension Who?, face match) read the same JSON the app writes:
#   Windows: %APPDATA%\Boomer Browse\loved-ones.json
# Electron sets BOOMER_USER_DATA to that folder when it starts the voice server; `npm run voice` alone uses the same default path.
# Override only if you store user data somewhere else:
# BOOMER_USER_DATA=C:\path\to\writable\folder

# --- HTTP API (browser extension, Loved ones, page scan) on port 3001 ---
# “Unable to connect” from curl means this process is not running. Start it and leave the terminal open:
#   From repo root:  npm run voice
#   (alias: npm run api)
# Or run Vite + API together:  npm run dev:all
# Electron (npm run electron:dev) starts the API when the app opens; closing Electron stops it.
# Test:  curl http://127.0.0.1:3001/extension/ping

# Extension “Scan this page” face match: install once in backend folder:
#   pip install -r requirements-face.txt
# Uses DeepFace (downloads models on first run).

# Persistent browser automation worker (browser_worker.py). If you see ModuleNotFoundError: browser_use:
#   pip install -r requirements-worker.txt
# To run the backend without the worker (no in-app browser tasks until installed):
# SKIP_BROWSER_WORKER=1
#
# Browser Use Cloud (hosted agent): if BROWSER_USE_API_KEY is set, /browser-automation uses the cloud API
# and the local Python worker is not started. Get a key from https://browser-use.com — see also
# https://docs.browser-use.com/cloud/agent/models
# Their API may require a minimum prepaid credit balance (e.g. $1) even on a “Free” plan—that is separate from Boomer.
# BROWSER_USE_API_KEY=bu_...
# Optional: bu-mini | bu-max (default bu-max), or another model string your project supports:
# BROWSER_USE_CLOUD_MODEL=bu-max
# Optional: max wait for the agent session to finish (ms, default 300000):
# BOOMER_BROWSER_USE_CLOUD_TIMEOUT_MS=300000
# Optional: HTTP client timeout per request (ms, default 120000):
# BROWSER_USE_HTTP_TIMEOUT_MS=120000
# OPENAI_API_KEY is optional with cloud mode; if set, vague tasks are still enriched from visit history before sending to the agent.
#
# If `python` on PATH is the wrong install, set the interpreter that has browser-use:
# PYTHON_BROWSER_WORKER=C:\Path\to\python.exe
#
# Voice (Vapi): add a function tool named add_reminder with JSON schema
#   { "type":"object","properties":{"title":{"type":"string"},"note":{"type":"string"},"dueAt":{"type":"string","description":"ISO8601 optional"}},"required":["title"] }
# so “remind me to …” saves to Daily reminders (GET/POST /reminders on this API).
#
# Holistic → voice: GET /vapi-config passes variableValues.boomer_holistic_context for {{boomer_holistic_context}} in the assistant system prompt.
# Populated from the last successful GET /cognitive/agentverse run (Cognitive insight card); no extra ASI call on connect.
# VAPI_HOLISTIC_CONTEXT=1
# Set to 0 or false to disable injection (empty string).
# VAPI_HOLISTIC_CONTEXT_MAX_CHARS=2400
